#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/rendering-animate-svg-wrapper.md
M|rules|title: Animate SVG Wrapper Instead of SVG Element
M|rules|impact: LOW
M|rules|impactDescription: enables hardware acceleration
M|rules|tags: rendering, svg, css, animation, performance
M|rules|Many browsers don't have hardware acceleration for CSS3 animations on SVG elements. Wrap SVG in a `<div>` and animate the wrapper instead.
M|rules|**Incorrect (animating SVG directly - no hardware acceleration):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function LoadingSpinner() {
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<svg
M|rules|className="animate-spin"
M|rules|width="24"
M|rules|height="24"
M|rules|viewBox="0 0 24 24"
M|rules|>
M|rules|<circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" stroke="currentColor" />
M|rules|</svg>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (animating wrapper div - hardware accelerated):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function LoadingSpinner() {
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<div className="animate-spin">
M|rules|<svg
M|rules|width="24"
M|rules|height="24"
M|rules|viewBox="0 0 24 24"
M|rules|>
M|rules|<circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" stroke="currentColor" />
M|rules|</svg>
M|rules|</div>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|This applies to all CSS transforms and transitions (`transform`, `opacity`, `translate`, `scale`, `rotate`). The wrapper div allows browsers to use GPU acceleration for smoother animations.